(71, 'Francis Fukuyama: Liberalism and Its Broken Promises | Endgame #116 (Luminaries)', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eq8CdeEOnhs', 'Gita Wirjawan', 61557, 'PT1H16S', 2014, '2023-01-20', 'Dr. Francis Fukuyama, an American political scientist and economist, dismantles the complex dynamics of liberalism, democracy, and communism—including its ideal concept, evolution, and growing threats. Moreover, the discussion touches on the foreseeable future of the Russia-Ukraine War, ASEAN, and China. Francis Fukuyama is the Olivier Nomellini Senior Fellow at Stanford University\'s Freeman Spogli Institute for International Studies (FSI). He is also the writer of the famous \"The End of History and the Last Man\" (1992), \"Liberalism and Its Discontents\" (2022), and \"Political Order and Political Decay\" (2014). About the host: Gita Wirjawan is an entrepreneur, educator, and currently a visiting scholar at Stanford University at the Walter H. Shorenstein Asia-Pacific Research Center (APARC). ----------------- Pre-Order the official Endgame merchandise: https://wa.me/628119182045 SGPP Indonesia Master of Public Policy 2022/24 admission: admissions.sgpp.ac.id admissions@sgpp.ac.id https://wa.me/628111522504 Other \"Endgame\" episode Playlist: https://endgame.id/season2 https://endgame.id/season1 https://endgame.id/thetake Listen in Spotify: https://endgame.id/spotify Visit and subscribe: @SGPPIndonesia @VisinemaPictures ----------------- 00:00 Grew Up with Philosophy 02:06 Evolution of Democracy 14:57 3 Arguments of Liberalism 21:38 Gap in Global Economy 30:28 Polarization & Social Media 38:38 \'Curing\' Democracy 53:28 Towards the Future', ''),
